We note that \emph{P}(4) is the statement ``4 is divisible by 4'', which
is true. We also note that \emph{Q}(4) is the statement ``17 is
divisible by 3'' which is false. As such, the implication

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle
P(4) \Rightarrow Q(4)
\end{align*}

does not hold, and so the statement

\begin{align*}
\forall\, n \in \mathbb{N}, P(n) \Rightarrow Q(n)
\end{align*}

is false.
